<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-8969] Parameter name data is erased when applying traits regardless of --parameters setting</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-8969</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When Groovy applies a trait to class it erases parameter name data. You can see this here:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/groovy/blob/982bd38b3216ea3143b0d667d2cd47d2c758f884/src/main/java/org/codehaus/groovy/transform/trait/TraitComposer.java#L157&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/groovy/blob/982bd38b3216ea3143b0d667d2cd47d2c758f884/src/main/java/org/codehaus/groovy/transform/trait/TraitComposer.java#L157&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So regardless whether `-parameters` is specified to the compiler traits will not retain parameter name information.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13211545">GROOVY-8969</key>
